{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/bakers-cyst/management/management/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"a75461ad-549a-5c00-a404-fcfeb6279a79","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field d28f6068-4208-42c3-8d96-4b8b9943d1d6 --><h2>Scenario: Management of Baker's cyst</h2><!-- end field d28f6068-4208-42c3-8d96-4b8b9943d1d6 -->","summary":"Covers the management of Baker's cyst in children and adults in primary care.","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item dc470552-30d6-4e48-8ca7-a801949fe000 --><!-- begin field a35d73c2-868e-4de3-99fd-acbc01558d81 --><p>From birth onwards.</p><!-- end field a35d73c2-868e-4de3-99fd-acbc01558d81 --><!-- end item dc470552-30d6-4e48-8ca7-a801949fe000 -->","topic":{"id":"827408d2-5101-5742-b5b5-208da85d4b2f","topicId":"6fa55009-ba10-4b15-b2fb-dd73ccd90892","topicName":"Baker's cyst","slug":"bakers-cyst","lastRevised":"Last revised in May 2020","chapters":[{"id":"cfb84d18-65ee-5c46-87e6-4f64eedf9678","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"14233c7c-90af-554c-aded-3ddb65b592f3","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"bc25fd1f-5061-5688-92eb-1bdf3f401790","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"76300a46-c213-5376-b46b-2b1045f39ef8","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"5d51256c-ab4d-5066-8384-aa73c9b7cf44","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"61f3f4ae-a264-52ae-a360-e9748770b3bf","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"32dc73e8-82ee-58f3-b7c2-09a3a20d706a","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"ee17499f-7234-51af-a9e0-260f95f59ae6","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"e4492913-e3d1-5aaa-8f16-abc3e2f65fcc","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"328699c7-7aa3-54ef-b3ba-b7b9fd19c8cd","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"9c7b02e9-c58c-5eec-b6c4-f7c798fc5d2c","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"95e4cf2f-083a-5af6-b153-690f02ec162a","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"84eec99c-112c-5365-8714-42ac56cf3514","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"c1927936-5646-5534-8137-b3be9ab89377","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"0bf6bcd3-ac81-508c-8e53-3b659afedb64","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"},{"id":"4d7eb346-e9d2-5ae3-991d-3be7d63362db","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"a12a65ee-44ce-5a25-b008-ac6ea71ed78e","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"},{"id":"3b3cf2f2-99cc-5e59-a7c3-a13b0350288e","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"}]},{"id":"70d892c0-8664-582c-b2a0-7466d4775825","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"e75e0f9f-54da-59db-8eae-3081f841823d","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},{"id":"ce10fada-1b22-5deb-9a2b-6bb1605e18e8","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"}]},{"id":"ddb63fac-a53c-551f-bf9c-a40cecbca194","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"a75461ad-549a-5c00-a404-fcfeb6279a79","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management"}]},{"id":"c2d2872e-c005-55ae-bd1a-3dfa73d33cc5","fullItemName":"Prescribing information","slug":"prescribing-information","subChapters":[{"id":"0fb395f5-f00f-5713-b568-9b41017c2c8e","slug":"paracetamol-nsaids","fullItemName":"Paracetamol and NSAIDS"}]},{"id":"78b2e19d-b236-55b8-bcd6-366cec1512bd","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"6508b4d6-128e-5d15-a883-01f141304d24","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"7b7d5068-9e40-51bf-aace-3f81e06e598c","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"addb76a5-08b9-5c32-8a82-5c514aff66b5","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"19eff0af-709f-531d-be9d-006591aa9c75","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"9800380c-0767-5100-b155-15c9c3804828","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"7c68b9e1-3032-51e1-b70f-9222a3f038cc","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"7a6c7872-3819-500f-9b4a-f798bb3efd07","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"ddb63fac-a53c-551f-bf9c-a40cecbca194","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Management"},"subChapters":[{"id":"bcc9d619-e6e9-5151-9739-ab165e4bc5e5","slug":"management-in-children","fullItemName":"Management in children","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field d4c2acfc-000e-4483-b9f6-a1f0f55e2429 --><h3>Management in children</h3><!-- end field d4c2acfc-000e-4483-b9f6-a1f0f55e2429 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item e1cbbf5a-f7e4-4fc1-a053-95b1fd436dc3 --><!-- begin field 74f84e30-07ac-4101-8b54-1de32e0ddef1 --><ul><li><strong>Admit to paediatrics or accident and emergency for urgent assessment </strong>if any red flags indicating a serious <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/diagnosis/differential-diagnosis/\">alternative diagnosis</a> (such as deep vein thrombosis) are identified in assessment.</li><li><strong>Consider referral:</strong><ul><li>To a paediatric orthopaedic surgeon, if symptomatic or the cyst is very large.</li><li>To a paediatric rheumatologist or paediatrician, if an underlying condition (such as inflammatory joint disease) is suspected.</li><li>To a paediatric orthopaedic surgeon or paediatrician, if diagnosis is unclear.</li></ul></li><li>If no underlying disease is suspected, and the diagnosis is confirmed on ultrasound scan, reassure the child (and the parents or carers) that primary Baker's cysts usually resolve without treatment.</li></ul><!-- end field 74f84e30-07ac-4101-8b54-1de32e0ddef1 --><!-- end item e1cbbf5a-f7e4-4fc1-a053-95b1fd436dc3 -->","subChapters":[{"id":"27a8568c-1f72-59d4-b00d-47024273a9d2","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-2bc","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":4,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 905e14a8-0562-4f00-b001-e9c3b1884d08 --><h4>Basis for recommendation</h4><!-- end field 905e14a8-0562-4f00-b001-e9c3b1884d08 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 2bcca7bd-520a-4ae2-ae9e-f191ee6db579 --><!-- begin field 08421b96-6664-460a-90c1-02c40a4a1355 --><p>The recommendations on management of Baker's cysts in children are based on expert opinion in review articles [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">Fritschy, 2006</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">Stein, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">Herman, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">Harcke, 2016</a>].</p><!-- end field 08421b96-6664-460a-90c1-02c40a4a1355 --><!-- end item 2bcca7bd-520a-4ae2-ae9e-f191ee6db579 -->","subChapters":[]}]},{"id":"115d53a8-bf54-5ccf-9895-0f7ff8d2efd6","slug":"management-in-adults","fullItemName":"Management in adults","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 4a3c203f-827d-49d6-8b45-a42e9e250235 --><h3>Management in adults</h3><!-- end field 4a3c203f-827d-49d6-8b45-a42e9e250235 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 85379e01-bedd-48d5-850e-f90973f5fbba --><!-- begin field 22b33fee-aca7-4a1b-af98-ff69f11db709 --><ul><li><strong>Arrange same-day assessment in secondary care if:</strong><ul><li>Any <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/diagnosis/diagnosis/\">red flags</a> are identified or there is a high index of suspicion of a serious <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/diagnosis/differential-diagnosis/\">alternative diagnosis</a>, such as deep vein thrombosis (DVT).</li></ul></li><li><strong>Identify and optimize management of any underlying condition.</strong><ul><li>See the CKS topics on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/gout/\">Gout</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/osteoarthritis/\">Osteoarthritis</a>, and <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/rheumatoid-arthritis/\">Rheumatoid arthritis</a> for further information.</li></ul></li><li><strong>If the cyst is asymptomatic, no treatment is required.</strong><ul><li>Explain that excision is generally not recommended as the Baker's cyst may resolve by treating any underlying condition.</li></ul></li><li><strong>If symptoms are troublesome: </strong><ul><li>Consider simple analgesia (such as paracetamol or ibuprofen) and physiotherapy — for further prescribing information see the CKS topics on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/analgesia-mild-to-moderate-pain/\">Analgesia - mild-to-moderate pain</a> and <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/nsaids-prescribing-issues/\">NSAIDs - prescribing issues</a>.</li><li>Direct aspiration of a Baker's cyst in primary care is not recommended<strong>.</strong></li></ul></li><li><strong>Consider referral to a rheumatologist or orthopaedic surgeon for further assessment and treatment if: </strong><ul><li>The diagnosis of a popliteal fossa swelling is unclear.</li><li>Symptoms are troublesome despite conservative measures, or the cyst is very large.</li><li>Specialist treatment of underlying disease of the knee joint is required.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Patient information on Baker's cyst is available from:</strong><ul><li>The NHS website \"<a href=\"http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/bakers-cyst\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hyperlink-id=\"71f98632-51c1-45ca-b79b-abc300f046eb\">Baker's cyst</a>\".</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 22b33fee-aca7-4a1b-af98-ff69f11db709 --><!-- end item 85379e01-bedd-48d5-850e-f90973f5fbba -->","subChapters":[{"id":"6d9d0066-d04c-566c-a3d4-743bdf6c1764","slug":"secondary-care-investigations-treatments","fullItemName":"Secondary care investigations and treatments","depth":4,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field c7169419-150d-44ae-83ea-8cc6254cd457 --><h4>Investigations and treatment in secondary care</h4><!-- end field c7169419-150d-44ae-83ea-8cc6254cd457 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 2d6563a5-f8f0-42bc-a53e-6392f9530882 --><!-- begin field 37e95481-fd20-4483-b328-961e6b9a31e1 --><ul><li><strong>Investigations in secondary care may include: </strong><ul><li>Magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) — for a more detailed evaluation of internal knee structures, and localization of the cyst.</li><li>Ultrasound-guided aspiration of the cyst — analysis and culture of fluid may be used to help distinguish between inflammatory, infectious, and mechanical processes.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Treatments that may be offered in secondary care include:</strong><ul><li>Aspiration of the knee effusion with or without intra-articular corticosteroid injection.</li><li>Cyst aspiration and intra-cystic corticosteroid injection.</li><li>Arthroscopy — to identify and treat any underlying joint pathology, for example, a meniscal tear.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Surgical interventions.</strong><ul><li>The main aim of surgery is to resolve any underlying joint pathology, such as meniscal tears or ligament damage, as treatment of underlying joint pathology can result in resolution of the cyst. Cyst excision is associated with a high rate of recurrence.</li></ul></li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">Fritschy, 2006</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">English, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">Snir, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">Stein, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">Herman, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">Harcke, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">BMJ Best Practice, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">Han, 2019</a>]</p><!-- end field 37e95481-fd20-4483-b328-961e6b9a31e1 --><!-- end item 2d6563a5-f8f0-42bc-a53e-6392f9530882 -->","subChapters":[]},{"id":"17f15c25-5908-5840-8327-5caf0cc263b4","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-fbb","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":4,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 5ff90a92-8cb6-4bad-b100-b1e46765c8c3 --><h4>Basis for recommendation</h4><!-- end field 5ff90a92-8cb6-4bad-b100-b1e46765c8c3 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item fbb4185a-d3be-476d-9755-f315dab240a5 --><!-- begin field 9b37411b-de8d-42a3-b4ad-1bdafb8c65a3 --><p>The recommendations on management of Baker's cysts in adults are based on expert opinion in review articles [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">Fritschy, 2006</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">English, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">Stein, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">Herman, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">BMJ Best Practice, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">Han, 2019</a>].</p><ul><li>Use of anticoagulants to treat suspected deep vein thrombosis (DVT) while waiting for ultrasound confirmation can lead to increased bleeding (and in some cases compartment syndrome) from a ruptured Baker’s cyst [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bakers-cyst/references/\">Herman, 2014</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 9b37411b-de8d-42a3-b4ad-1bdafb8c65a3 --><!-- end item fbb4185a-d3be-476d-9755-f315dab240a5 -->","subChapters":[]}]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}